translate ru JaeidPath5_a935db16:
    # "In the days that followed, Sarah slowly adapted a routine."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_6e07b916:
    # "It wasn't much, she was grateful for the small distractions that it offered her."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_7856c72a:
    # "She found that whenever she worked, her mind was too busy to worry about the bigger things in her life."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_c890d0db:
    # "Too distracted for grief."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_2bdb3535:
    # "Outside of keeping the house clean, she had also offered to do most of the shopping as well."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_414a2d90:
    # "Initially, Jaeid had been hestitant, but Jasmine had pushed him to let her go."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_a9d44646:
    # "Sarah was happy that she could go to the market."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_b3f51aa5:
    # "It was one more way in which she could be useful, and at the same time, it allowed her to explore the city."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_d1d6e06d:
    # "Sarah knew that escaping was dangerous, but if she even wanted to have the option, she would need to learn more about the city."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_cde7c537:
    # "Even in these few days, she had learned plenty."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_df179a20:
    # "She learned the layout of the city of Al'Gahaem. Where the markets were, the soldier districts, the political district."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_bec665e9:
    # "As well as the slave pens."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_1e207c3c:
    # "Sarah had passed that wicked place a few times. Afraid to even look at it directly, she could only glance from the corner of her eyes."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_f64e450d:
    # "Looking back from the cages, the hollowed out eyes of the slaves."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_7b8e8b5c:
    # "They were dragged out by start of day for work and brought back most evenings."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_c474aa8f:
    # "She could only speculate where each of them came from, but for many, the answer was obvious."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_b1c770f0:
    # "Their skin and hair like hers, her broken people."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_35b08f25:
    # "Sarah averted her gaze and went back to walking towards the markets."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_7be5ba61:
    # "She could hear the buzzing of the crowds grow louder as she came closer to the market section."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_b498a359:
    # "This was one of the smaller markets, more specialized in different kinds of food. Some of the other markets dealt in just about anything."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_e72f15d1:
    # "To her surprise, the merchants were nearly as diverse as the slaves."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_52463c68:
    # "The Tribesmen did not simply value strength, it was the only principle by which they lived."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_2a9d4cc6:
    # "A man who wielded no sword was no man at all in their eyes."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_082e70eb:
    # "A merchant, in their eyes, was as low as any man could be. Earning his way through life by trickery and deceit."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_e73ae358:
    # "But this caused no conflict in the world of the Tribesmen."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_7f851a8d:
    # "For only the foreigners were merchants, and they had never held them in high regards."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_2d318c78:
    # "And while they might not respect the merchants, every warrior of the Tribe did value the ability to trade away their loot for something they wanted."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_4daa9b15:
    # "Thus, while the Tribesmen had little respect for merchants, they oddly allowed them to thrive in relative safety."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_9cf58fde:
    # "This was part of what made Al'Gahaem into the trading hub that it was."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_6b855cc2:
    # "Stepping into the market, Sarah could feel the market on every sense."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_6ad35485:
    # "The noise of the crowd. The smell of the spices. The heat on her body."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_c4a174d2:
    # "This being one of the smaller markets, she could more easily walk through the crowd."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_17f710bd:
    # "At the larger markets, the crowds could grow so thick, one had to almost push themselves through the people."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_5090c21d:
    # "And given Sarah's strength, it was hard not to be swept up by the crowd."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_cd0be46d:
    # "As she walked further along the markets and inspected the first of the stalls, Sarah slowly made an inventory in her mind."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_46c5dd3d:
    # "She would come back to them later. It was bad luck to buy the first thing you saw."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_cacec3bc:
    # "To her wonder, there were even stalls with fish."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_d2cea9dc:
    # "How they managed to get those here, fresh and well, countless miles from the ocean, she'd never know."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_41cda533:
    # "As she moved through the crowd, she could spot the occasional glance."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_7053ae2c:
    # "She had become herself surprised by how quickly she had learned to wear the slave outfit without thinking about it."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_c30018a2:
    # "If she had worn a thing like this in Rosanna...unthinkable."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_ac156caf:
    # "But here, as a slave, she was hardly worth their attention."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_7397c650:
    # "What attention she did earn was the same she had always endured. The wandering eyes of men."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_7313a2e4:
    # "And here their hands wandered as their eyes did."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_3fb2c2b1:
    # "More than once, she would feel a hand, graze her skin or cup her ass."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_bb340171:
    # "Again, in Rosanna, they would have paid dearly for it."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_f3a23850:
    # "Here, Sarah knew she could not so much as raise an objection. She had no rights against them."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_790bc04c:
    # s "Dahaehm...aeyah...khayin..."
    s ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_5e07c152:
    # "Sarah spoke the words slowly and in a broken accent."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_97792f9e:
    # "Jasmine had taught her the most basic of words in the language of the Tribes, and Sarah did her best to imitate it."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_19d53386:
    # "Sarah learned that if she spoke slowly and clearly, and repeated herself many times, eventually they would understand."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_89c836f2:
    # "What she could not communicate in words, she communicated with gestures."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_78286354:
    # "It wasn't perfect, but it managed."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_0d64dabb:
    # "The merchant nodded to her broken speech and laid out some bags of rice."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_40aa162e:
    # "Sarah nodded."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_a153141f:
    # s "Aaah!"
    s ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_13c761c8:
    # "Sarah suddenly cried out and spun around in shock."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_6f08f346:
    # "The man behind her was smiling as he looked at her."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_2669d6d1:
    # "He had pinched her ass and Sarah could still feel the sting."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_7494c2bd:
    # "For a moment, rage roared up in her chest."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_609c1de4:
    # "She wanted to punch him. She wanted to do a lot of things."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_83bbcea2:
    # "Sarah could also instantly see he was a Tribesman. Far above her in station."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_800f2bfc:
    # "Instead of all her anger, other words came out."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_42268146:
    # s "I'm...sorry."
    s ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_57d59429:
    # "She tried to turn around but before she could he had grabbed her wrist."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_6ff5274e:
    # "Fighting him off was no option. Not only was he stronger than her by far, but striking him would not end well for her."
    ""

translate ru JaeidPath5_f755ce25:
    # "Sarah could feel him begin to pull her away from the market stall."
    ""

